entries.title: Guatemala Widens Prosecutions Against Former Anticorruption Officials
entries.description: The moves have fueled concerns among the U.S. government and rights groups about democratic backsliding in Guatemala.

entries.title: Berlin Won't Allow Exports of German Tanks to Ukraine Unless U.S. Sends Own Tanks
entries.description: North Atlantic Treaty Organization allies have over 2,000 German-made Leopard tanks.

entries.title: Israel's Supreme Court Strikes Down Appointment of  Netanyahu Ally
entries.description: Judges found the appointment of Shas leader Aryeh Deri as a minister “extremely unreasonable” given his conviction for tax evasion last year.

entries.title: Ukraine Helicopter Crash Kills Interior Minister and at Least 13 Others in Kyiv
entries.description: Denys Monastyrsky and other senior officials were among at least 14 people killed when a helicopter crashed near a kindergarten on the edge of Kyiv, Ukrainian officials said.

entries.title: Russian Spy or Ukrainian Hero? The Strange Death of Denys Kiryeyev
entries.description: Hours before Russia sent troops into Ukraine last February, Mr. Kiryeyev warned of Moscow’s plan to capture Kyiv. Days later, he was killed by security agents.”If it were not for Mr. Kiryeyev, most likely Kyiv would have been taken.”

entries.title: Global Minimum Tax Could Bring Governments Higher Revenues Than Thought
entries.description: Governments could get a bigger windfall than previously estimated if they implement a planned overhaul of international tax rules, according to the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development.

entries.title: Church of England Bishops Decline to Back Same-Sex Marriage
entries.description: LGBT weddings won’t be allowed to take place in church, but priests will be able to bless couples married in a civil ceremony, the Church decided after a six-year debate on the issue.

entries.title: Sicilian Mafia's Bloodiest Era Draws to a Close With Arrest of Old-School Boss
entries.description: The crime syndicate has largely retreated to its native island, but its members still enjoy a strong support network.
